# cedar-authz-service — REST Client requests
# Requires the VS Code extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client).
# Usage: start the stack (docker compose up --build), then click "Send Request"
# above any request below. Edit the variables to try your own cases.
#
# Expected decisions mirror scripts/demo.sh:
#   forbid overrides permit -> carol (admin) is still DENIED the confidential
#   "secret" doc, while alice (its owner) is ALLOWED.

@host = http://localhost:8080

# Variables for the playground request (edit freely)
@principal = bob
@action = view
@resource = design

### Health — should return { ok: true, cedar_version: "..." }
GET {{host}}/health

### Playground — authorize using the @principal/@action/@resource variables above
# @name playground
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "{{principal}}",
  "action": "{{action}}",
  "resource": "{{resource}}"
}

### 1. alice view design  ->  ALLOW  (owner + group)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "alice",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "design"
}

### 2. bob view design  ->  ALLOW  (group -> folder -> doc)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "bob",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "design"
}

### 3. bob edit design  ->  DENY  (group only grants view)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "bob",
  "action": "edit",
  "resource": "design"
}

### 4. dave view design  ->  DENY  (no relationship at all)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "dave",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "design"
}

### 5. carol view design  ->  ALLOW  (admin role)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "carol",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "design"
}

### 6. bob view secret  ->  DENY  (confidential, not owner)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "bob",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "secret"
}

### 7. carol view secret  ->  DENY  (forbid overrides admin!)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "carol",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "secret"
}

### 8. alice view secret  ->  ALLOW  (owner overrides confidential)
POST {{host}}/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "principal": "alice",
  "action": "view",
  "resource": "secret"
}
